Here’s a multi-language code showcase with five formats — including one plain text block with no markdown fencing:

### 🐍 Python

```python
def hello():
    print("Hello from Python!")

```

### 🦫 Go (Golang)

```go
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
    fmt.Println("Hello from Go!")
}

```

### 🐚 Bash

```bash
#!/bin/bash
echo "Hello from Bash!"

```

### 🧪 TypeScript

```typescript
function greet(name: string): string {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

console.log(greet("TypeScript"));

```

### 📄 Plain Text (no markdown block)

def hello():
print("Hello from plain text Python!")

